Delaware could be among the first states to use mobile drivers licenses.

The Delaware Division of Motor Vehicles has launched a mobile drivers license pilot study that will run for six months, according to a release from the Delaware Department of Transportation.

The six-month pilot study will include about 200 state employees and stakeholders.

Delaware is among the first states to test a mobile drivers license, and were excited to help move this new technology forward, said Gov. John Carney said in the release.